tcela-19 is an MPEG-1 bitstream designed for testing that MPEG-2
decoders can decode properly MPEG-1 constrained bitstreams with
picture horizontal size equal to 768.

This bitstream will be added to the MPEG-2 Video Conformance Testing
bitstream set.  Test bistream ID should be #32 (ID not approved yet).

According to the MPEG-2 Video IS (section 8.1), Simple, Main, SNR
scalable, Spatial scalable and High profile decoders at Main level or
better shall be able to decode this bitstream.

Parameters are the following:

Description:    An MPEG-1 constrained bitstream with picture horizontal
                size equal to 768;

Purpose:  Check that decoder can decode ISO/IEC 11172-2 constrained
parameter bitstreams with the maximum horizontal_size allowed when
constrained_parameter_flag = 1.

Parameters:     MPEG-1, 31 frames
Organization:   TCE-LA

All parameters are within the range allowed for MPEG-1 constrained bitstreams.
Bit rate:               1.856000 Mbit/sec 
Sampling dimensions:    768  x 128 x 23.976 Hz

Please check that you can decode it.  Thank-you.

        Bitstream file             tcela-19.bits
        Reconstructed frames*      tcela-19.decoded
        Decoding trace **          tcela-19.trace (first 4 frames)
        picture structure          I0 P3 B1 B2 P6 B4 B5...

        *frame format:

                4:2:0 frame ("display" order) 8 bit

                       width
                +---------------+
                |               |
                |      Y0       | height
                |width/2        |
                +-------+-------+
                |  Cb0  | height/2
                +-------+
                |  Cr0  | height/2
                +-------+-------+
                |               |
                |      Y1       |
                |               |
                +-------+-------+
                |       |
                  etc...

        ** Only the first row of MBs is traced.
           More complete traces are available on special order.


Best regards,

Tristan

